      "writtenOn": "2018-05-05T02:26:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is it actually not possible to implicitly default a oneof?\n\nI find it surprising that setting multiple members of a oneof is silently ignored rather than being a runtime error:\nhttps://developers.google.com/protocol-buffers/docs/reference/python-generated#oneof\n\nGiven such behavior I would not be extra surprised if they also had something strange like \"whichever oneof you look at first is auto-initialized\".",
      "revId": "481e78f2cded17ebc9e17a1a2220a061d94cd469",
